data.name: ENFJ_Description
data.value: People who share the Protagonist personality type feel more at home when they are in a relationship, and few types are more eager to make a romantic commitment to their chosen partner. The protagonists take dating and relationships seriously, selecting partners with a long-term view rather than the more casual approach you might expect from some Explorer types. There is no greater joy for the Protagonists than helping towards the goals of someone they care about, and the intertwining of lives that a committed relationship represents is the perfect opportunity to do just that.

data.name: ENFP_Description
data.value: When it comes to relationships, there's hardly anyone around who's more excited than Campaigners to share with their partners the abundance of insightful insights and experiences life has to offer. For people with the Campaigners personality type, relationships are a joyful process of mutual exploration and imagination, a chance to connect with another soul. Campaigners take their relationships seriously and are known for their uninhibited and unwavering devotion to the people to whom they have committed their hearts.

data.name: ENTJ_Description
data.value: As in other areas of their lives, commanders approach dating and relationships with a set of goals and a plan to achieve them, and they do so with impressive energy and enthusiasm. People with the Commander personality type want to win and will gladly take on leadership roles in relationships early on, taking personal responsibility for how things go and actively working to ensure a mutually rewarding experience. Romantic relationships are serious business, and commanders have been at it for a long time.

data.name: ENTP_Description
data.value: If there's one thing Debaters are good at, it's coming up with a never-ending stream of innovations and ideas to keep things moving forward, and that's evident in their romantic relationships as well. For people with the Breakthrough personality type, growth is key, and even before they find a dating partner, they imagine all the ways they can try new things together, to grow together. This can be an overwhelming process if your partner doesn't respond, but when Innovators find someone who shares their love of intellectual exploration, beware.

data.name: ESFJ_Description
data.value: Valuing social validation and a sense of belonging so highly, romantic relationships hold a special level of importance for consuls. No other relationship type provides people with the Consul personality type the same level of support and devotion, and the feelings of security and stability that accompany strong romantic relationships are extremely warm.

data.name: ESFP_Description
data.value: Entertainers are sociable, fun-loving and free-spirited people who live life in the moment and extract every bit of emotion from everything. Naturally, they spare none of that freshness and energy in dating. For people with the Entertainer personality type, relationships aren't about slowly building the groundwork for the future or planning a life - they're bubbly, unpredictable things to enjoy as long as there's pleasure to be had.

data.name: ESTJ_Description
data.value: Executives are quite unique in the sense that their relationships don't really change as they progress from the dating phase to more stable, long-term relationships and even further into marriage. Because they value honesty and openness so much, people with an executive personality tend to be clear about who they are, what they are like, and what their goals are from the start, and they should follow through on these statements for the long haul. As long as your partner is able to take your word for it and follow suit, they tend to be extremely stable relationships.

data.name: ESTP_Description
data.value: When it comes to romantic relationships, it can hardly be said that people with the Enterprising personality type are missing their wedding day. Life is fun and full of surprises (something entrepreneurs have a knack for delivering), and they enjoy everything here and now. Entrepreneurs may not spend a lot of time planning “someday,” but their enthusiasm and unpredictability make them exciting dating partners.

data.name: INFJ_Description
data.value: Advocates (INFJs) tend to take the process of finding a romantic partner seriously. People with this personality type seek depth and meaning in their relationships, preferring not to settle for a union that is based on anything less than true love. It can take some time for Advocates to find a compatible partner. Some people may think Advocates are too demanding and it's true that these personalities can have unrealistic expectations. Some Advocates may expect a 'perfect' partner or relationship that ultimately does not exist.

data.name: INFP_Description
data.value: Mediators (INFPs) are dreamers and idealists, especially when it comes to romance. The concept of true love resonates with them, and they are unlikely to be happy in a relationship based on anything less. People with this personality type may daydream about the perfect relationship, imagining what it would be like to share their innermost self with another person.

data.name: INTJ_Description
data.value: Architects (INTJs) approach romance the way they do most challenges: strategically, with clear-cut goals and a plan for achieving them. In a purely rational world, this approach would be foolproof. Alas, love is rarely rational, and Architects are at risk of overlooking or misinterpreting the unpredictability of human nature and affection.

data.name: INTP_Description
data.value: When it comes to romantic relationships, logicians have an interesting mix of traits that often pleasantly surprise their partners. People with this personality type are always full of ideas, but have little opportunity to explore their more romantic notions. As with any of their theories, logicians love to share with others, and when they finally meet someone where romantic thoughts are appropriate, they are excited, enthusiastic, and even playful, flirting with wordplay and intellectual play.

data.name: ISFJ_Description
data.value: When it comes to romantic relationships, the kindness of the Defenders turns into a joy that is only found in taking care of your family and home, in being there for emotional and practical support whenever needed. Home is where the heart is for people with the Defender personality type, and in no other area of their lives do they strive so hard to create the harmony and beauty they want to see in the world.

data.name: ISFP_Description
data.value: Adventurers are quite mysterious and hard to get to know. Although they are very emotional individuals, they guard this sensitive core carefully, preferring to listen rather than express. People with the Adventurer personality type focus on their partners, with little interest in dictating the mood of a situation with their own feelings. While this can sometimes be frustrating, if they are accepted for what they are, Adventurers prove to be warm and enthusiastic partners.

data.name: ISTJ_Description
data.value: Logisticians are totally trustworthy and this trait is clearly expressed when it comes to their romantic relationships. Often representing the epitome of family values, people with the Logistics personality type are comfortable with, and often even encourage, traditional domestic and gender roles, and look for a family structure guided by clear expectations and honesty. While their reserved nature often makes dating logisticians a challenge, they are truly dedicated partners, willing to put a lot of thought and energy into ensuring stable, mutually satisfying relationships.

data.name: ISTP_Description
data.value: When it comes to romantic relationships with Virtuosos, it's a bit like nailing jelly to a tree. Dating personalities Virtuoso is a tango, complex and interesting, with alternating coldness and detachment, and passion, spontaneity and pleasure of the moment. Nothing can be forced in Virtuoso relationships, but as long as they are given the space they need to be themselves, they will be happy to enjoy the comfort of a stable partner for life.
